criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Have nonspecific chronic neck pain, defined as a recurrent or persistent pain that
             lasts more than 3 months, with no trauma or etiology/diagnosis associated.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Visual and hearing dysfunction not corrected by eyeglasses/contact lenses or a hearing
             aid;

          -  Infectious diseases;

          -  Cervical myelopathy;

          -  Cervical surgery;

          -  Cervical fracture or/and subluxation;

          -  Vestibular pathology;

          -  Neurological disorder/deficits;

          -  Rheumatic autoimmune diseases;

          -  History of cancer;

          -  Severe cervical trauma.
